#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.66"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.66:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.66:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.66:0.3"
msgid "66. Sāḷhasutta"
msgstr "66. With Sāḷha and Friends"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an3.66:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an3.66:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā nandako sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Nandaka was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern "
"Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother."

#. VAR: migāranattā sāṇo ca sekhuniyanattā → rohaṇo ca pekhuniyanattā (bj) | rohano ca pekhuṇiyanattā (s1-3, km) | rohaṇo ca pekhuṇiyanattā (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.66:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sāḷho ca migāranattā sāṇo ca sekhuniyanattā yenāyasmā nandako "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ nandakaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sāḷhaṃ migāranattāraṃ āyasmā nandako "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Sāḷha, Migāra’s grandson, and Rohaṇa, Pekhuṇiya’s grandson went up to "
"Venerable Nandaka, bowed, and sat down to one side. Then Venerable Nandaka "
"said to Sāḷha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.194"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Etha tumhe, sāḷhā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, Sāḷha and friends, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by "
"lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely "
"on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t "
"go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the "
"appearance of competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected "
"teacher.’"

msgctxt "an3.66:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yadā tumhe, sāḷhā, attanāva jāneyyātha ‘ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā "
"sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya "
"dukkhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, sāḷhā, pajaheyyātha."
msgstr ""
"But when you know for yourselves: ‘These things are unskillful, blameworthy, "
"criticized by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to "
"harm and suffering’, then you should give them up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sāḷha? "

msgctxt "an3.66:3.2"
msgid "atthi lobho”ti?"
msgstr "Is greed real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:4.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:5.1"
msgid "“Abhijjhāti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Covetousness’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:5.2"
msgid ""
"Luddho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, abhijjhālu pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, "
"paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa "
"hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A person who is greedy and covetous kills living creatures, steals, commits "
"adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:6.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:7.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sāḷha? "

msgctxt "an3.66:7.2"
msgid "atthi doso”ti?"
msgstr "Is hate real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:8.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:9.1"
msgid "“Byāpādoti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Ill will’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:9.2"
msgid ""
"Duṭṭho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, byāpannacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, "
"paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa "
"hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A hateful and malicious person kills living creatures, steals, commits "
"adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:10.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:11.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sāḷha? "

msgctxt "an3.66:11.2"
msgid "atthi moho”ti?"
msgstr "Is delusion real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:12.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:13.1"
msgid "“Avijjāti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Ignorance’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:13.2"
msgid ""
"Mūḷho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, avijjāgato pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, "
"paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa "
"hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A person who is deluded and ignorant kills living creatures, steals, commits "
"adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:14.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:15.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“What do you think, Sāḷha, are these things skillful or unskillful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:16.1"
msgid "“Akusalā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Unskillful, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:17.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:18.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Blameworthy, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:19.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:20.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Criticized by sensible people, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:21.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti, no vā?"
msgstr "“When you undertake them, do they lead to harm and suffering, or not?”"

msgctxt "an3.66:21.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.195"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:22.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti."
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering."

msgctxt "an3.66:22.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how we see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:23.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, sāḷhā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā:"
msgstr "“So, Sāḷha and friends, when we said:"

msgctxt "an3.66:23.2"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, sāḷhā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please, Sāḷha, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go "
"by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t "
"rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the "
"acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of "
"competence, and don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”"

msgctxt "an3.66:23.3"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, sāḷhā, attanāva jāneyyātha—"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.66:23.4"
msgid ""
"ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā "
"samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, sāḷhā, "
"pajaheyyāthā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"“These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, "
"and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering”, then you "
"should give them up.’"

msgctxt "an3.66:23.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "that’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:24.1"
msgid ""
"Etha tumhe, sāḷhā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"Please, Sāḷha, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go "
"by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t "
"rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the "
"acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of "
"competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’"

msgctxt "an3.66:24.2"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, sāḷhā, attanāva jāneyyātha:"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.66:24.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, sāḷhā, "
"upasampajja vihareyyātha."
msgstr ""
"‘These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when "
"you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness’, then you should "
"acquire them and keep them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:25.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, atthi alobho”ti?"
msgstr "What do you think? Is contentment real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:26.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:27.1"
msgid "“Anabhijjhāti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Satisfaction’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:27.2"
msgid ""
"Aluddho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, anabhijjhālu neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, "
"na paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, parampi na tathattāya samādapeti, "
"yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A person who is content and satisfied doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, "
"commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting welfare and happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:28.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:29.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, atthi adoso”ti?"
msgstr "What do you think? Is love real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:30.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:31.1"
msgid "“Abyāpādoti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Good will’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:31.2"
msgid ""
"Aduṭṭho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, abyāpannacitto neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ "
"ādiyati, na paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, parampi na tathattāya "
"samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A loving and kind-hearted person doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, "
"commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting welfare and happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:32.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:33.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sāḷha? "

msgctxt "an3.66:33.2"
msgid "atthi amoho”ti?"
msgstr "Is understanding real?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:34.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.196"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:35.1"
msgid "“Vijjāti kho ahaṃ, sāḷhā, etamatthaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“‘Knowledge’ is what I mean by this."

msgctxt "an3.66:35.2"
msgid ""
"Amūḷho kho ayaṃ, sāḷhā, vijjāgato neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na "
"paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, parampi na tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ "
"sa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A person who understands and knows doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, "
"commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. Is that for their "
"lasting welfare and happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:36.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:37.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sāḷhā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“What do you think, Sāḷha, are these things skillful or unskillful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:38.1"
msgid "“Kusalā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Skillful, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:39.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:40.1"
msgid "“Anavajjā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Blameless, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:41.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:42.1"
msgid "“Viññuppasatthā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Praised by sensible people, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:43.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti, no vā?"
msgstr ""
"“When you undertake them, do they lead to welfare and happiness, or not?"

msgctxt "an3.66:43.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:44.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantīti."
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness."

msgctxt "an3.66:44.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how we see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:45.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, sāḷhā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā:"
msgstr "“So, Sāḷha and friends, when we said:"

msgctxt "an3.66:45.2"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, sāḷhā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by "
"testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely "
"on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance "
"of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and "
"don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”"

msgctxt "an3.66:45.3"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, sāḷhā, attanāva jāneyyātha—"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.66:45.4"
msgid ""
"ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantīti, atha "
"tumhe, sāḷhā, upasampajja vihareyyāthā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"“These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when "
"you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness”, then you should "
"acquire them and keep them.’ "

msgctxt "an3.66:45.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.197"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:46.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, sāḷhā, ariyasāvako evaṃ vigatābhijjho vigatabyāpādo asammūḷho "
"sampajāno patissato mettāsahagatena cetasā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Then that noble disciple is rid of desire, rid of ill will, unconfused, "
"aware, and mindful. They meditate spreading a heart full of love …"

msgctxt "an3.66:46.2"
msgid "karuṇā …"
msgstr "compassion …"

msgctxt "an3.66:46.3"
msgid "muditā …"
msgstr "rejoicing …"

msgctxt "an3.66:46.4"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyāpajjhena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the "
"fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they "
"spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an3.66:46.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.66:46.6"
msgid ""
"‘atthi idaṃ, atthi hīnaṃ, atthi paṇītaṃ, atthi imassa saññāgatassa uttari "
"nissaraṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘There is this, there is what is worse than this, there is what is better "
"than this, and there is an escape beyond the scope of perception.’"

msgctxt "an3.66:46.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati;"
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "an3.66:46.8"
msgid "vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "an3.66:46.9"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "an3.66:47.1"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "an3.66:47.2"
msgid "‘ahu pubbe lobho, tadahu akusalaṃ, so etarahi natthi, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘Formerly there was greed, which was unskillful. Now there is none, so that’"
"s skillful."

msgctxt "an3.66:47.3"
msgid "ahu pubbe doso … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Formerly there was hate, which was unskillful. Now there is none, so that’s "
"skillful."

msgctxt "an3.66:47.4"
msgid "ahu pubbe moho, tadahu akusalaṃ, so etarahi natthi, iccetaṃ kusalan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Formerly there was delusion, which was unskillful. Now there is none, so "
"that’s skillful.’"

msgctxt "an3.66:47.5"
msgid ""
"So diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītibhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī "
"brahmabhūtena attanā viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"So they live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, "
"experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.66:47.6"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
